    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\n**Root cause:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.\n\n### The Bug\n```typescript\n// processItems() in src/utils.ts, line 7\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {  // ← - 1 is wrong\n```\nThe `- 1` means the loop only runs up to index `n-2`, completely skipping the last element.\n\n### The Fix — one character change\n```typescript\n// Remove the \" - 1\"\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n```\n\n### Verification\nRun `npm test` — all 6 tests in `tests/utils.test.ts` should pass. The three failing tests (`all items`, `single item`, `two items`) all exercise the off-by-one scenario directly.",
